Package: appblocker
Version: 0.14.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: AppBlocker <appblocker@example.com>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.6), python3-tk, policykit-1, wmctrl
Recommends: python3-pil, python3-pystray
Homepage: https://github.com/asondh/Linux-app-blocker
Description: Parent-friendly application blocker with timers and schedules
 AppBlocker lets a parent block applications (especially web browsers) for
 their children, machine-wide, without sudo gymnastics. A root systemd
 service enforces a shared blocklist for every user and starts on boot.
 .
 Features include manual / timer / weekly-schedule blocks, per-user
 targeting, and auto-block rules ("while app X runs for a child, block apps
 Y and Z for them"). The admin GUI opens via a graphical polkit prompt so
 children cannot change settings.
